init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the US President informing the world that even though the US is still in ruins, it has decided to come out of isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Because we were in isolation, the world had advanced much faster than we had and we soon found ourselves struggling to catch up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There were also giant cities in the sky and even people invited to come and stay there.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: and even people invited to come and stay there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States quickly learned that the world had continued to advance and it was no longer the center of technological and military supremacy.
